{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849105419,"sessionID":"ses_287270f86ffeSemVNN1czfTDNb","part":{"id":"prt_d78dae7dc001xXYczaDAYrzFaE","messageID":"msg_d78d9be6d001hM1rLruf5UqWpk","sessionID":"ses_287270f86ffeSemVNN1czfTDNb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-608b3eccbb8d469a978bed4c765ec7f0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","content":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that:\n\n1. **Session Resolution**: Reads session ID from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager when missing\n2. **Reverse Proxy**: Forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`\n3. **JWT Authentication**: Generates RS256-signed JWT tokens for `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` kinds\n4. **Activity Tracking**: Updates session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle timeout detection\n5. **Concurrency Control**: Limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware to prevent overload\n6. **Health Endpoints**: Exposes `/health/live` and `/health/ready` for Kubernetes probes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle management |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct (Port, EnableTLS, TLSCert, TLSKey, MaxConcurrentRequests, Debug) |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface, manager struct with workload manager client |\n| `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Reverse proxy with custom Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation, token signing, K8s Secret persistence |\n| `pkg/router/handlers.go` | `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/v1/...invocations/*path` handlers |\n| `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limit middleware using buffered channel semaphore |\n| `pkg/router/errors.go` | Error types: SessionNotFoundError, SandboxUnreachableError, TimeoutError |\n| `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server construction, route registration, TLS, health endpoints tests |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Session resolution, workload manager create, error mapping tests |\n| `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Proxy director, forwarding headers, path normalization tests |\n| `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT generation, RS256 signing, secret persistence tests |\n\n### Key Components\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── Server (server.go)\n│   ├── Config struct (Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests, Debug)\n│   ├── gin.Engine setup with mode (Debug/Release)\n│   ├── Route registration (health, invocation routes)\n│   ├── http.Server with h2c, ReadTimeout 30s, IdleTimeout 90s\n│   ├── Start(ctx) with graceful shutdown (10s deadline)\n│   └── Dependencies: SessionManager, Store, JWTManager, http.Transport\n│\n├── SessionManager (session_manager.go)\n│   ├── Interface: GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)\n│   ├── manager struct with storeClient, workloadMgrAddr, httpClient\n│   ├── NewSessionManager: reads WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL (required)\n│   ├── createSandbox: POST to Workload Manager with optional K8s SA token\n│   └── HTTP client: Timeout 2m, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 config\n│\n├── Reverse Proxy (reverse_proxy.go)\n│   ├── httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy\n│   ├── Director: path normalization, Host, forwarding headers, JWT\n│   ├── ModifyResponse: x-agentcube-session-id header injection\n│   ├── ErrorHandler: connection refused → 502, timeout → 504\n│   └── Entry point matching from SandboxInfo.EntryPoints\n│\n├── JWT Manager (jwt.go)\n│   ├── RSA 2048-bit key generation (PKCS1 private, PKIX public)\n│   ├── GenerateToken: exp (5m), iat, iss=\"agentcube-router\", custom claims\n│   ├── TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret: K8s Secret persistence/reuse\n│   └── RS256 signing with golang-jwt/v5\n│\n├── Middleware (middleware.go)\n│   ├── concurrencyLimitMiddleware: buffered channel semaphore\n│   ├── MaxConcurrentRequests capacity (default 1000 when ≤0)\n│   └── 429 response when overloaded: SERVER_OVERLOADED code\n│\n└── Handlers (handlers.go)\n    ├── handleHealthLive: 200 {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n    ├── handleHealthReady: 200/503 based on sessionManager nil\n    ├── handleInvoke: session resolution → proxy → activity update\n    └── Error mapping: APIStatus → appropriate HTTP code\n```\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Workload Manager implementation (covered by AR-00x)\n- Store implementation (covered by session-store spec)\n- Kubernetes Reconciler (AR-007)\n- Prometheus metrics export\n- Distributed session cache (Redis cluster)\n- WebSocket upgrade handling\n- Custom retry logic for failed proxies\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `pkg/store` | Store interface for session lookup, UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n| `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CR types |\n| `client-go` | kubernetes.Interface for JWT Secret management |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for routing and middleware |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | RS256 JWT signing |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | h2c server configuration |\n| Workload Manager service | POST `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter` for sandbox creation |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | CLI entry point, flag parsing, Server construction |\n| Kubernetes Deployment | Router as reverse proxy front-end to sandbox pods |\n| SDK/CLI clients | Invocation requests routed through Router |\n| `pkg/agentd` (idle cleanup) | Last-activity timestamps for idle detection |\n| Kubernetes probes | `/health/live`, `/health/ready` endpoints |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Session Header Name**: `x-agentcube-session-id` header is contract; changing breaks all clients\n- **JWT Secret Name**: `picod-router-identity` Secret; migration needed if renamed\n- **Invocation Route Pattern**: `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` is fixed\n- **Response Header**: `x-agentcube-session-id` on proxied responses is client expectation\n- **Default Concurrency Limit**: 1000 when `MaxConcurrentRequests ≤ 0`; affects throughput under load\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Envoy Sidecar Proxy\n\n**Approach**: Deploy Envoy as sidecar to handle routing and load balancing.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Production-grade proxy; rich routing features; observability built-in |\n| Cons | Heavy sidecar; no session-aware routing; requires xDS control plane; JWT signing complex |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Session-aware routing requires custom logic that Envoy cannot natively provide. In-process Go reverse proxy offers tighter integration with session management.\n\n### Alternative 2: Nginx Ingress with Lua\n\n**Approach**: Use Nginx Ingress with Lua scripts for session routing and JWT injection.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | High performance; widely deployed; Nginx ecosystem |\n| Cons | Lua scripting complexity; no native store integration; debugging harder; JWT requires external helper |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Go-based proxy provides native integration with `pkg/store`, `pkg/common/types`, and Kubernetes client-go. Lua-based approach lacks tight coupling needed for session lifecycle.\n\n### Alternative 3: API Gateway (Kong/Traefik)\n\n**Approach**: Use Kong or Traefik as API gateway for routing.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Plugin ecosystem; declarative config; multi-protocol support |\n| Cons | External dependency; session store integration via plugin; JWT plugin limitations |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires session-stateful routing with direct store access. External gateway adds operational complexity and latency.\n\n### Alternative 4: Custom HTTP Router with FastHTTP\n\n**Approach**: Use `fasthttp` instead of `net/http` for higher performance.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Lower latency; zero-allocation design; high throughput |\n| Cons | Different API from `net/http`; httputil.ReverseProxy incompatible; Gin ecosystem mismatch |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. `net/http` compatibility is required for `httputil.ReverseProxy` and Kubernetes client libraries. Gin middleware ecosystem (cors, recovery) is well-supported. Performance targets met with current stack.\n\n### Alternative 5: Session-less Direct Routing\n\n**Approach**: Clients directly invoke sandbox pods without session abstraction.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No session state; simpler architecture |\n| Cons | Clients must track pod endpoints; no idle timeout; no JWT injection; breaks SDK abstraction |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Session abstraction is core to AgentCube design—clients use logical names (namespace/name) while Router handles physical routing (pod IPs) and lifecycle (creation/expiry).\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Sandbox pod unreachable (connection refused) | ErrorHandler maps to 502 `sandbox unreachable` |\n| Sandbox timeout during proxy | ErrorHandler maps to 504 `sandbox timeout` |\n| JWT signing failure | Respond 500 with `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` code |\n| Workload Manager unavailable | Startup fails if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` missing; retry logic in session manager |\n| Secret creation race (multiple routers) | `AlreadyExists` handled by loading existing secret |\n| Concurrency limit exhaustion | 429 with `SERVER_OVERLOADED` code; client retry |\n| TLS misconfiguration | Start returns error if cert/key missing when `EnableTLS=true` |\n| Session not found in store | 404 with `SessionNotFoundError` |\n| Entry points empty | 404 `no entry point found for sandbox` |\n| Path normalization missing leading slash | Director prefixes `/` if needed |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Constants**: `rsaKeySize=2048`, `jwtExpiration=5m`, `IdentitySecretName=\"picod-router-identity\"`\n2. **HTTP2**: `h2c` server with `http2.Server` for non-TLS HTTP/2 support\n3. **Transport**: `IdleConnTimeout=0`, `DisableCompression=false`, shared across all proxies\n4. **Session Manager HTTP Client**: `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`, HTTP2 with `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n5. **Workload Manager Auth**: Reads `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` for in-cluster auth\n6. **Environment Variables**: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required), `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (optional, default=\"default\")\n7. **Last-Activity Updates**: Twice per invoke—after sandbox resolution and after proxy completion\n8. **Graceful Shutdown**: 10s deadline on context cancel\n9. **Route Pattern**: Both GET and POST on invocation routes\n\n## References\n\n- `session-routing/spec.md` - Full requirement specification\n- `session-routing/design.md` - Detailed design document\n- `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response types\n- `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client code reference\n- `project.md` - AgentCube architecture overview\n- `httputil.ReverseProxy`: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http/httputil#ReverseProxy\n- `golang-jwt/v5`: https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/router.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":49,"character":49},"end":{"line":49,"character":60}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod 